    "docHtml": "<p>A mining tool with two opposed heads—a sharp point and a flat adze—hafted to five feet, pressed into war-service to crack armor and stone alike. The point punches through mail and plate; the adze chops or levers. Slow and unwieldy for a duelist, but deadly in the press of a siege or tunnel-breach where armor clusters thick.</p>\n",
